dance beyond the usual scaffold. The compile failure is due to an API change, not setup issues. It seems like I should provide an advisory note saying that \\\"Lucene core 6.0.0 is self-contained.\\\" Important elements include defining environment variables and system properties, along with ensuring that any custom AttributeImpl implements reflectWith. This feels crucial for a successful javac compile.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating risks in testing**\\n\\nI need to consider that the old tests calling MMapDirectory internals could depend on encapsulated APIs, so local verification is critical. Normally, Lucene core indexing utilizes analyzers from lucene-analyzers-common for StandardAnalyzer examples. However, adding this would expand the scope unnecessarily since lucene-core already covers the base Analyzer, TokenStream, and core fields. I should definitely highlight this risk in the evaluation and ensure that the JSON is a valid single object.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"lucene-core 6.0.0 is a self-contained core artifact with no Maven runtime dependencies and no external service requirement; the needed preparation is test-code/JVM guidance for Lucene 6 API changes and JDK-internal access used by existing meaningful coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not add lucene-analyzers-common or other Lucene modules just to reach lucene-core coverage. Keep coverage focused on classes present in lucene-core. For custom AttributeImpl subclasses, Lucene 6 makes reflectWith(AttributeReflector) abstract, so tests must implement it explicitly. If tests exercise MMapDirectory/RamUsageEstimator-style internals, keep the test JVM/native execution opens used by the existing Lucene tests: --add-opens=java.base/java.nio=ALL-UNNAMED and --add-opens=java.base/jdk.internal.ref=ALL-UNNAMED.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Lucene examples often use StandardAnalyzer from lucene-analyzers-common, but that is outside lucene-core and should not be added unless a specific test intentionally covers cross-module integration.\",\n    \"Native Image/JDK encapsulation behavior around MMapDirectory unmapping and RamUsageEstimator remains sensitive to JDK version; local Gradle and Native Image verification are authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c03c6e3f557fcd5016a3f9f5a8f848193a9726c68d401fe3f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3663, "output": 814, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31101, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782554447339, "responseId": "resp_0c03c6e3f557fcd5016a3f9f4feedc81938cff073518357705"}}
